# Off-nav docs pages — exempt from check-docs-nav-reachable's front-matter floor
# and reachability walk. One repo-relative path per line; '#' comments.
# A page belongs here only when it is off-nav by design: an embedded data
# fragment no link targets, or an immutable dated post — whether rendered
# front-matter-less through jekyll-optional-front-matter (docs/_config.yml) or
# carrying its own front matter (a release note's `release:` key) — whose inbound
# link is external (the GitHub Release), not a nav slot.
docs/evidence-data.md
docs/posts/2026-07-09-announcing-checkwright.md
docs/posts/2026-07-14-checkwright-v0-1-0.md
